messages.content: ComfyUI-TrollSuite is a suite of custom nodes for ComfyUI that includes BinaryImageMask, ImagePadding, LoadLastImage, RandomMask, and TransparentImage.
Which node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite allows loading the last generated image?
The LoadLastImage node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite allows loading the last generated image in ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of the RandomMask node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite?
The RandomMask node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used to generate random masks for image generation.
Which node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used for adding padding to images?
The ImagePadding node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used for adding padding to images in ComfyUI.
What is the function of the BinaryImageMask node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite?
The BinaryImageMask node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used to create binary masks for images.
Which node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used for handling transparent images?
The TransparentImage node in ComfyUI-TrollSuite is used for handling transparent images in ComfyUI.
How many custom nodes are included in ComfyUI-TrollSuite?
ComfyUI-TrollSuite includes a total of five custom nodes.
